sections.heading: Guard; fire department or district membership or service; effect on duty
sections.text: No member of the Nebraska National Guard shall be exempt or relieved from duty by membership or service in any fire department or district.SourceLaws 1909, c. 90, ยง 65, p. 385;R.S.1913, ยง 3900;C.S.1922, ยง 3298;C.S.1929, ยง 55-10
